profile_positions.description:
Dirk Rinze has been working on projects in the UAE, Kuwait and several in London, all designed by diverse well-known architects, like:

* Jameel Arts Centre in Dubai, UAE (Serie Architects);
* Stratford Waterfront redevelopment (Olympicopolis) in London, UK (Allies and Morrison);
* Tottenham Hotspur Football Club in London, UK (Populous);
* Regeneration of the Battersea Power Station site in London, UK (Foster + Partners);
* Feasibility studies;
* International Design Competitions.

Dirk Rinze has worked on two projects in Qatar, one project in the UAE, one in Saudi Arabia and two refurbishment projects in London, all designed by diverse well-known architects, like:

* Al Shaqab Training Track in Doha, Qatar (David Chipperfield Architects);
* Al Shaqab Hotel Resort & Spa in Doha, Qatar (David Chipperfield Architects);
* Jameel Arts Centre in Dubai, UAE (Serie Architects).

Dirk Rinze has been working on numerous projects for Van Rossum Raadgevende Ingenieurs, like:

* Hotel Crowne Plaza Amstelkwartier in Amsterdam, the Netherlands (Paul de Ruiter and Mulderblauw Architecten);
* Angstelzight (parking, supermarket and housing) in Abcoude (Van Moort & Partners Architecten);
* Boelelaan 30 a.k.a. Stage Entertainment in Amsterdam (AMA Group Architecten);
* Het Rond (city hall, apartments, parking) in Zeist, the Netherlands (RAU Architects);
* Hotel Ramada Apollo Amsterdam Centre in Amsterdam, the Netherlands (ZZDP Architecten);
* Hotelschool The Hague in Amsterdam, the Netherlands (ZZDP Architecten);
* Various (international) design competitions;
* Various Seconds Opinions.

During the employement at Ove Arup & Partners, Dirk Rinze has worked on both Spanish as Dutch (colaborated with the Amsterdam Office) projects:

* Five stars hotel ArcoSur in Torremolinos, Spain (Arqui-Concept);
* New construction of the offices for IB Group and Tax Service in Groningen, the Netherlands (UNStudio);
* New construction of and renovation for headquarters BBVA in Madrid,Spain (Herzog & De Meuron);
* New construction of the District Military Police at Schiphol, the Netherlands (Zvi Hecker Architekt);
* Football stadium Valencia CF in Valencia, Spain (Reid Fenwick Asociados);
* Renovation at & expansion of the estate De Horst in Driebergen, the Netherlands (Ontwerpgroep Trude Hooykaas);
* Dutch Institute of Ecology in Wageningen, the Netherlands (Claus en Kaan Architecten);
* Park Hyatt Cap Vermell on Mallorca, Spain (DSA Architects International);
* Campus Iberdola in San Agustin del Guadalix, Spain (Alonso Balaguer y Arquitectos Asociados).

Dirk Rinze has worked on numerous projects during his employment at Pieters Bouwtechniek in Utrecht, the Netherlands. A small selection has been visualized below:

* Traffic bridge Suytkade in Helmond, the Netherlands (Soeters Van Eldonk Architecten);
* Restoration of the monumental villa Oranjelust in Utrecht, the Netherlands (OPL Architecten);
* Station area Kop van Kessel-Lo in Leuven, Belgium (SeARCH Architects in combination with AR-TE);
* Energy efficient office building in Olso, Norway (SeARCH Architects);
* Bicycle storage at the train station in Zutphen, the Netherlands (S2 Architecten);
* Town hall Texel in Den Burg, the Netherlands (Architectenburo Alberts & Van Huut);
* Harbour pavilion Dichterswijk-West in Utrecht, the Netherlands (Architectenbureau Sluijmer en Van Leeuwen in combination with Metname);
* Shopping center Markthof in Hoofddorp, the Netherlands (De Architecten Cie);
* Seventeen business units Floridadreef in Utrecht, the Netherlands (Cita Architecten);
* Residential complex Dichterswijk-West in Utrecht, the Netherlands (Maccreanor & Lavington Architects);
* Residence Vaillantlaan on IJburg, the Netherlands (Korteknie Stuhlmacher Architecten).

During the internship Dirk Rinze has worked on: 

* Theatre and dancehall Teatro del Canal in Madrid, Spain (Juan Navarro Baldeweg);
* Highrise Torre Espacio in Madrid, Spain (Pei, Cobb, Freed &amp; Partners);
* Highrise Torre Mare Nostrum in Barcelona, Spain (Enric Miralles and Benedetta Tagliabue);
* Congress center Foro Sur in Valencia, Spain (José María Tornás Llavador);
* Footbridge in Valladolid, Spain (Rafael Moneo and Enrique de Teresa).
